&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Wrike is the most powerful work management platform. Built for teams and organizations looking to collaborate, create, and exceed every day, Wrike brings everyone and all work into a single place to remove complexity, increase productivity, and free people up to focus on their most purposeful work.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our vision:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;A world where everyone is free to focus on their most purposeful work, together.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wrike is building a new generation of engineers who pair solid Java fundamentals with genuine, hands-on AI fluency. This isn’t a fixed lane for a 10-year veteran. It’s a newly created talent track for someone who already builds with AI as a natural part of their job- and wants to grow into full end-to-end ownership over the next year or two, with a clear, supported path to do so.&lt;br&gt;We evaluate this role on what you’ve actually built and how you work, not on years of tenure. If you have a strong Java base and real curiosity about AI-assisted development- not just awareness of it- this is worth a conversation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll sit inside one of our cross-functional Scrum teams and work on real product features from day one- not isolated tickets handed down with every decision pre-made. You’ll get more ownership as you demonstrate it: starting with clearly-scoped backend work and growing toward the kind of end-to-end, full-stack ownership our senior builders have.&lt;br&gt;AI tools are not optional here. You’re expected to work AI-native from day one: using them daily as part of your toolkit, experimenting, and deliberately getting better at AI-assisted development to remove friction from your workflow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and ship backend features in Java/Spring, with growing exposure to the full stack as you take on more scope across modern frontend technologies (TypeScript, React 19) and legacy components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with AI coding tools (Cursor, Claude/Codex, our internal AI portal, and MCP) as a daily part of how you build- experimenting and finding new ways to save real time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write automated tests, take part in code reviews, and contribute to task estimation and technical planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate an existing, living codebase- learning what to reuse, where rebuilding makes sense, and how to hold the line against tech debt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take increasing ownership of features as you build trust- this is a growth track designed to transition you into a full end-to-end owner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with senior engineers and teams, picking up the critical thinking and judgment calls that come with full system ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid foundation in backend engineering, with comfort in Java (21), Spring, REST APIs, and SQL, TypeScript, React 19&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine curiosity about and active use of AI coding tools- not avoidance, not just “awareness,” but a desire to push past the learning curve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of things you’ve actually built and shipped, even at a smaller scope- we care more about what you’ve done than your title or years of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growth mindset: comfortable navigating a non-trivial codebase and taking on more ambiguity as you prove you can handle it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good collaboration instincts- you ask questions, raise issues early, and work seamlessly within a cross-functional team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our stack:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Java (21), Spring, REST APIs,

